<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05032l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05032l">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05032l"> 32(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Arius = Luther</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">All Pannonia was at that time devastated by the Arian heresy, and even certain bishops and priests dared openly to deny the Godhead of our Lord Jesus Christ and His consubstantiality with the Father and the Holy Ghost. <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 23-24</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Arius was a heresiarch of the 3rd-4th century. Luther was a church-reformer from the 15th-16th century.  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c02032e" href="c02all.htm#c02032e">VI.C.02:032(e)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
